# Masterboard runs fully client-side; per-GM runtime config (GitHub PAT, repo,
# Imgur client id, source-site URLs) is entered in the app's Settings and stored
# encrypted in IndexedDB — never here, never committed.
#
# The one build-time value is the tldraw license key. tldraw DISABLES its editor
# on production deployments (https + non-localhost, e.g. GitHub Pages) unless a
# key is provided — the Session planner board goes blank a few seconds after it
# loads without one. Get a FREE, watermarked key at https://tldraw.dev and set it
# here for local prod builds, and as a build variable in CI (see the deploy
# workflow). The key is domain-scoped and ships in the client bundle, so it is
# safe to expose publicly. Local dev on http://localhost does not need it.
VITE_TLDRAW_LICENSE_KEY=
